{
  "texts": [
    "Adversarial training as in Eq. 21",
    "The objective of the discriminator is to maximize its confidence in identifying a sample from the true distribution q(y t-1 |y t) while minimizing its confidence in identifying a fake sample from p θ (y t-1 |y t).",
    "Conversely, the genera- tor aims to increase the likelihood that the fake samples it produces are classified as genuine by the discriminator.",
    "(15) q y t | y 0 = N y t; ᾱt y 0, (1 -ᾱt)I",
    "Please note that the formula above requires an unknown distribution, q y t-1 y t, in order to obtain samples."
  ]
}